GoogleRpcStatus.description: The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the [API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors).

GoogleTypeDate.description: Represents a whole or partial calendar date, such as a birthday. The time of day and time zone are either specified elsewhere or are insignificant. The date is relative to the Gregorian Calendar. This can represent one of the following: * A full date, with non-zero year, month, and day values * A month and day, with a zero year (e.g., an anniversary) * A year on its own, with a zero month and a zero day * A year and month, with a zero day (e.g., a credit card expiration date) Related types: * google.type.TimeOfDay * google.type.DateTime * google.protobuf.Timestamp

month.description: Month of a year. Must be from 1 to 12, or 0 to specify a year without a month and day.

day.description: Day of a month. Must be from 1 to 31 and valid for the year and month, or 0 to specify a year by itself or a year and month where the day isn't significant.

year.description: Year of the date. Must be from 1 to 9999, or 0 to specify a date without a year.
